00:25:12.660 --> 00:25:13.460 align:middle line:90%
What can they do?

00:25:13.460 --> 00:25:16.232 align:middle line:90%


00:25:16.232 --> 00:25:17.160 align:middle line:90%
[SIGH]

00:25:17.160 --> 00:25:19.370 align:middle line:90%
>> They need to unpack it.

00:25:19.370 --> 00:25:23.040 align:middle line:90%
They need to verbalize it.

00:25:23.040 --> 00:25:29.430 align:middle line:84%
There's nothing in my opinion
more valuable, more healing--

00:25:29.430 --> 00:25:31.985 align:middle line:84%
not downloading your story,
but sharing your story.

00:25:31.985 --> 00:25:33.360 align:middle line:84%
Sharing it with
people you trust,

00:25:33.360 --> 00:25:35.840 align:middle line:90%
sharing it with strangers.

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:39.740 align:middle line:84%
At the very least,
going to therapy.

00:25:39.740 --> 00:25:42.040 align:middle line:84%
I remember the first
time I went to therapy,

00:25:42.040 --> 00:25:44.280 align:middle line:90%
and I didn't need therapy.

00:25:44.280 --> 00:25:45.572 align:middle line:90%
I was way too cool for therapy.

00:25:45.572 --> 00:25:47.197 align:middle line:84%
I was going because
I was just curious.

00:25:47.197 --> 00:25:48.810 align:middle line:84%
And I went to see
this guy and I said,

00:25:48.810 --> 00:25:51.165 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to see how you work.

00:25:51.165 --> 00:25:52.290 align:middle line:90%
And I walked into the room.

00:25:52.290 --> 00:25:53.700 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not sure I've shared
this story with you, James.

00:25:53.700 --> 00:25:56.790 align:middle line:84%
But I walked into the room,
and there was two chairs.

00:25:56.790 --> 00:25:59.250 align:middle line:84%
And one had the
biggest box of Kleenex

00:25:59.250 --> 00:26:00.933 align:middle line:90%
I've ever seen in my life.

00:26:00.933 --> 00:26:02.850 align:middle line:84%
It looked like must have
been a wholesale box,

00:26:02.850 --> 00:26:04.870 align:middle line:90%
like a stack of them.

00:26:04.870 --> 00:26:08.065 align:middle line:90%
And I sat in the other chair.

00:26:08.065 --> 00:26:08.940 align:middle line:90%
And the guy walks in.

00:26:08.940 --> 00:26:09.660 align:middle line:90%
He goes, sorry.

00:26:09.660 --> 00:26:10.440 align:middle line:90%
That's my chair.

00:26:10.440 --> 00:26:11.020 align:middle line:90%
And I sat down.

00:26:11.020 --> 00:26:12.562 align:middle line:84%
It was like a "Jerry
Maguire" moment.

00:26:12.562 --> 00:26:15.030 align:middle line:84%
And I look at the Kleenex and
I'm thinking to myself, pfft.

00:26:15.030 --> 00:26:16.240 align:middle line:90%
Not a chance, buddy.

00:26:16.240 --> 00:26:17.040 align:middle line:90%
Crying?

00:26:17.040 --> 00:26:18.730 align:middle line:90%
Me?

00:26:18.730 --> 00:26:20.800 align:middle line:84%
I'd say two and a
half minutes in,

00:26:20.800 --> 00:26:24.730 align:middle line:84%
I was vibrating and oscillating
between complete sadness

00:26:24.730 --> 00:26:27.880 align:middle line:84%
that I've never experience in
my life before and absolute rage

00:26:27.880 --> 00:26:30.510 align:middle line:84%
and anger towards
myself and the world.

00:26:30.510 --> 00:26:31.310 align:middle line:90%
I was shocked.

00:26:31.310 --> 00:26:32.110 align:middle line:90%
I was stunned.

00:26:32.110 --> 00:26:34.120 align:middle line:90%
I was frightened.

00:26:34.120 --> 00:26:37.180 align:middle line:84%
And yet, I believed that
I didn't need the help.

00:26:37.180 --> 00:26:39.650 align:middle line:84%
I believed there wasn't
even a story to impact.

00:26:39.650 --> 00:26:43.060 align:middle line:84%
And if there was, it's
not that significant.

00:26:43.060 --> 00:26:45.040 align:middle line:84%
And over that period
of time I realized

00:26:45.040 --> 00:26:48.480 align:middle line:84%
the burden I was carrying,
the heaviness I was carrying.

00:26:48.480 --> 00:26:50.650 align:middle line:84%
And everything in my
life was representative

00:26:50.650 --> 00:26:51.943 align:middle line:90%
of what was going on.

00:26:51.943 --> 00:26:53.860 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't giving myself
permission to feel love

00:26:53.860 --> 00:26:56.170 align:middle line:84%
and to experience
love and to give love.

00:26:56.170 --> 00:26:59.290 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't giving myself
permission to even imagine

00:26:59.290 --> 00:27:02.800 align:middle line:84%
what it would be like to have
a good job that I enjoyed,

00:27:02.800 --> 00:27:06.440 align:middle line:84%
or start a business, or do
a speech, or write a book,

00:27:06.440 --> 00:27:08.450 align:middle line:90%
or anything.

00:27:08.450 --> 00:27:12.070 align:middle line:84%
Everything was
contracted and closed.

00:27:12.070 --> 00:27:15.100 align:middle line:84%
And week by week, month
by month, day by day,

00:27:15.100 --> 00:27:16.870 align:middle line:84%
whatever you want
to call it, I just

00:27:16.870 --> 00:27:19.660 align:middle line:84%
started letting go of more
and more and more stuff

00:27:19.660 --> 00:27:22.000 align:middle line:84%
and emerging on the
other side and feeling

00:27:22.000 --> 00:27:24.010 align:middle line:90%
lighter and more available.

00:27:24.010 --> 00:27:26.260 align:middle line:84%
And the possibilities
started to emerge

00:27:26.260 --> 00:27:27.720 align:middle line:90%
that I couldn't see before.

00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:30.170 align:middle line:84%
And I believe it's
directly related.

00:27:30.170 --> 00:27:31.420 align:middle line:90%
You need to unpack your story.

00:27:31.420 --> 00:27:34.270 align:middle line:84%
You need to understand the
cost of what you went through.

00:27:34.270 --> 00:27:35.830 align:middle line:84%
So many of us said,
yeah, OK, yeah.

00:27:35.830 --> 00:27:36.820 align:middle line:90%
My dad shouted at me.

00:27:36.820 --> 00:27:38.650 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, he hit me a few times.

00:27:38.650 --> 00:27:40.150 align:middle line:90%
And here's the classic.

00:27:40.150 --> 00:27:42.120 align:middle line:90%
Because that was the generation.

00:27:42.120 --> 00:27:44.830 align:middle line:90%
That's what they did.

00:27:44.830 --> 00:27:48.040 align:middle line:90%
My dad had that with his father.

00:27:48.040 --> 00:27:51.225 align:middle line:90%
My father did the best he could.

00:27:51.225 --> 00:27:52.600 align:middle line:10%
And the problem
there-- and maybe

00:27:52.600 --> 00:27:57.250 align:middle line:10%
he did-- but we need to isolate
the trauma from the person.

00:27:57.250 --> 00:27:58.750 align:middle line:84%
And if you can
understand the trauma

00:27:58.750 --> 00:28:03.980 align:middle line:84%
and how it affected you
away from the individual,

00:28:03.980 --> 00:28:06.590 align:middle line:84%
one is it allows you to
understand who you are

00:28:06.590 --> 00:28:10.390 align:middle line:84%
and how you are the way you
are today, and what drives you,

00:28:10.390 --> 00:28:11.930 align:middle line:90%
and what holds you back.

00:28:11.930 --> 00:28:15.350 align:middle line:84%
And secondly is it allows you
to heal the relationship that

00:28:15.350 --> 00:28:18.110 align:middle line:84%
has caused this to
begin with, and allows

00:28:18.110 --> 00:28:19.880 align:middle line:84%
you to create empathy
and understanding

00:28:19.880 --> 00:28:22.380 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what that person
was going through at that time.

00:28:22.380 --> 00:28:25.060 align:middle line:90%


00:28:25.060 --> 00:28:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>> To get to that place takes
time and takes awareness,

00:28:28.180 --> 00:28:30.970 align:middle line:84%
because I think this concept
of hurt people hurt people is

00:28:30.970 --> 00:28:33.640 align:middle line:84%
something that we don't
really acknowledge very much.

00:28:33.640 --> 00:28:37.330 align:middle line:84%
We say that, well, my father did
that because he was an asshole,

00:28:37.330 --> 00:28:42.760 align:middle line:84%
or that he was just a
mean person whereas,

00:28:42.760 --> 00:28:45.165 align:middle line:90%
how did he become like that?

00:28:45.165 --> 00:28:48.032 align:middle line:84%
What lineage did he have of his
experience and his childhood?

00:28:48.032 --> 00:28:49.990 align:middle line:84%
I think these are
interesting questions to ask.

00:28:49.990 --> 00:28:53.063 align:middle line:84%
Is that something that you often
find when people do that work?

00:28:53.063 --> 00:28:53.980 align:middle line:90%
They're like, oh, wow.

00:28:53.980 --> 00:28:56.020 align:middle line:84%
I realize why my
dad was like that.

00:28:56.020 --> 00:28:59.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think there's so much
anger and judgment present when

00:28:59.560 --> 00:29:01.460 align:middle line:84%
the trauma has not
been addressed.

00:29:01.460 --> 00:29:03.910 align:middle line:84%
So they're not ready
to even entertain

00:29:03.910 --> 00:29:06.610 align:middle line:84%
the idea of why their father did
what they did or their mother

00:29:06.610 --> 00:29:07.410 align:middle line:90%
did what they did.

00:29:07.410 --> 00:29:09.952 align:middle line:84%
But when they can start to heal
the trauma within themselves,

00:29:09.952 --> 00:29:12.040 align:middle line:84%
separate it from the
individual, and they

00:29:12.040 --> 00:29:15.160 align:middle line:84%
can start moving through
some of the stories,

00:29:15.160 --> 00:29:18.100 align:middle line:84%
they can start integrating the
rest of it and living with it

00:29:18.100 --> 00:29:19.670 align:middle line:84%
and seeing that
there is an upside--

00:29:19.670 --> 00:29:24.400 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that is a very, very,
very sensitive subject when

00:29:24.400 --> 00:29:26.050 align:middle line:84%
you say, when you
present the idea

00:29:26.050 --> 00:29:28.330 align:middle line:84%
that perhaps some goodness
came from the trauma

00:29:28.330 --> 00:29:29.592 align:middle line:90%
that you've experienced.

00:29:29.592 --> 00:29:31.300 align:middle line:84%
And people have to be
ready to hear that,

00:29:31.300 --> 00:29:32.710 align:middle line:90%
and ready to receive that.

00:29:32.710 --> 00:29:34.240 align:middle line:90%
And then they're open.

00:29:34.240 --> 00:29:36.850 align:middle line:84%
When they start to see there's
something good in this,

00:29:36.850 --> 00:29:39.850 align:middle line:84%
there's a learning in this,
there's an awareness in this,

00:29:39.850 --> 00:29:42.610 align:middle line:84%
then they're ready to go back to
the father they haven't spoken

00:29:42.610 --> 00:29:45.770 align:middle line:84%
in 10 years, the mother
they have ostracized out

00:29:45.770 --> 00:29:46.570 align:middle line:90%
of their life.

00:29:46.570 --> 00:29:48.550 align:middle line:84%
And even the ones
that have passed away,

00:29:48.550 --> 00:29:50.200 align:middle line:90%
and to create healing there.

00:29:50.200 --> 00:29:54.220 align:middle line:84%
And some of the greatest joy I
get is when I hear the stories.

00:29:54.220 --> 00:29:58.210 align:middle line:84%
My father or myself are talking
for the first time in 10 years.

00:29:58.210 --> 00:30:00.460 align:middle line:84%
And I got a man recently
to do something.

00:30:00.460 --> 00:30:03.850 align:middle line:84%
He's got a very estranged,
volatile relationship

00:30:03.850 --> 00:30:04.698 align:middle line:90%
with his father.

00:30:04.698 --> 00:30:06.490 align:middle line:84%
And he could sit in
front of me and tell me

00:30:06.490 --> 00:30:09.910 align:middle line:84%
stories that when he crashed his
father's motorbike many years

00:30:09.910 --> 00:30:14.470 align:middle line:84%
ago, his father came to the
scene, got the motorbike,

00:30:14.470 --> 00:30:19.570 align:middle line:84%
threw it in his truck,
absolutely ripped him apart.

00:30:19.570 --> 00:30:25.150 align:middle line:84%
-- left him on the side of the
street and tore off in his car.

00:30:25.150 --> 00:30:26.940 align:middle line:90%
And that was the anger speaking.

00:30:26.940 --> 00:30:28.510 align:middle line:84%
And when we moved
through the anger,

00:30:28.510 --> 00:30:31.900 align:middle line:84%
we moved through the trauma,
we moved through the hurt,

00:30:31.900 --> 00:30:34.910 align:middle line:84%
I asked him to tell
me that story again.

00:30:34.910 --> 00:30:37.503 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, you know,
I wasn't hit by another car,

00:30:37.503 --> 00:30:38.920 align:middle line:84%
because that's
what I told my dad.

00:30:38.920 --> 00:30:40.795 align:middle line:84%
I was driving too fast
and my father knew it.

00:30:40.795 --> 00:30:44.483 align:middle line:90%


00:30:44.483 --> 00:30:46.900 align:middle line:84%
I said, what about having that
conversation with your dad?

00:30:46.900 --> 00:30:48.780 align:middle line:90%
And he wrote a letter.

00:30:48.780 --> 00:30:51.340 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him to
write the letter

00:30:51.340 --> 00:30:54.160 align:middle line:84%
and allow me to read
it with his permission,

00:30:54.160 --> 00:30:56.155 align:middle line:84%
to take out some of
the little snipes,

00:30:56.155 --> 00:30:57.530 align:middle line:84%
things like, well,
I did my best,

00:30:57.530 --> 00:30:58.905 align:middle line:84%
and because you
were never there.

00:30:58.905 --> 00:31:00.070 align:middle line:90%
You know that dig?

00:31:00.070 --> 00:31:02.650 align:middle line:90%
And I just asked him, go first.

00:31:02.650 --> 00:31:04.320 align:middle line:90%
Just go first.

00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:06.620 align:middle line:84%
And he said, do you
remember that bike?

00:31:06.620 --> 00:31:09.245 align:middle line:84%
I was driving too fast,
but you know that already,

00:31:09.245 --> 00:31:10.832 align:middle line:90%
and I'm sorry.

00:31:10.832 --> 00:31:12.850 align:middle line:90%
Do you remember this?

00:31:12.850 --> 00:31:13.660 align:middle line:90%
I lied to you.

00:31:13.660 --> 00:31:15.226 align:middle line:90%
I'm sorry.

00:31:15.226 --> 00:31:17.650 align:middle line:90%
Do you remember that?

00:31:17.650 --> 00:31:19.933 align:middle line:90%
That's not true, Dad.

00:31:19.933 --> 00:31:21.850 align:middle line:84%
I did all this because
I wanted your attention

00:31:21.850 --> 00:31:23.082 align:middle line:90%
and I wanted your love.

00:31:23.082 --> 00:31:24.790 align:middle line:84%
And the reason he
didn't write the letter

00:31:24.790 --> 00:31:26.260 align:middle line:84%
and he didn't want
to write the letter

00:31:26.260 --> 00:31:27.635 align:middle line:84%
is at the end of
it he just said,

00:31:27.635 --> 00:31:30.340 align:middle line:90%
I want a relationship with you.

00:31:30.340 --> 00:31:33.820 align:middle line:84%
If this is something you
want with me, let me know.

00:31:33.820 --> 00:31:38.950 align:middle line:84%
He was afraid of the answer
coming back being, no.

00:31:38.950 --> 00:31:42.680 align:middle line:84%
He got a phone call within an
hour of that letter arriving,

00:31:42.680 --> 00:31:46.860 align:middle line:84%
and they had the conversation,
the conversation that he never

00:31:46.860 --> 00:31:50.004 align:middle line:84%
imagined would
happen in his life.

00:31:50.004 --> 00:31:52.960 align:middle line:90%
Ever.

00:31:52.960 --> 00:31:54.600 align:middle line:90%
I have a father who--

00:31:54.600 --> 00:31:55.870 align:middle line:90%
we've been fortunate.

00:31:55.870 --> 00:31:57.470 align:middle line:90%
And it's not me.

00:31:57.470 --> 00:32:00.490 align:middle line:84%
Whatever is coming
through me, whatever I do,

00:32:00.490 --> 00:32:01.955 align:middle line:90%
I don't even know what it is.

00:32:01.955 --> 00:32:04.080 align:middle line:84%
And we get lots of
testimonials, and this and that.

00:32:04.080 --> 00:32:06.180 align:middle line:84%
But we got a letter
from a man one day.

00:32:06.180 --> 00:32:10.033 align:middle line:84%
Thank you for giving
me my son back.

00:32:10.033 --> 00:32:12.200 align:middle line:84%
Because the son came back
after this week in Ireland

00:32:12.200 --> 00:32:14.640 align:middle line:84%
and sat with his
father and went first.

00:32:14.640 --> 00:32:16.265 align:middle line:10%
And I do this
exercise, and I say

00:32:16.265 --> 00:32:20.120 align:middle line:10%
to people, name one
relationship in your life

00:32:20.120 --> 00:32:21.200 align:middle line:10%
that you want to deepen.

00:32:21.200 --> 00:32:23.790 align:middle line:90%
One relationship.

00:32:23.790 --> 00:32:26.250 align:middle line:84%
Despite the fact-- and
this is the key piece--

00:32:26.250 --> 00:32:28.590 align:middle line:84%
whether they have ever
demonstrated a desire

00:32:28.590 --> 00:32:31.350 align:middle line:84%
to deepen it, are capable of
deepening it, because people--

00:32:31.350 --> 00:32:33.180 align:middle line:90%
oh, you don't know my father.

00:32:33.180 --> 00:32:35.160 align:middle line:90%
You haven't met my mother.

00:32:35.160 --> 00:32:36.120 align:middle line:90%
They're human.

00:32:36.120 --> 00:32:39.300 align:middle line:84%
Trust me, I have a
fairly good handle on it.

00:32:39.300 --> 00:32:43.210 align:middle line:84%
Pick the person you
almost don't want to pick.

00:32:43.210 --> 00:32:45.540 align:middle line:84%
Then I ask them to
identify, what is the thing

00:32:45.540 --> 00:32:46.870 align:middle line:90%
that that person needs to do?

00:32:46.870 --> 00:32:47.670 align:middle line:90%
Not you.

00:32:47.670 --> 00:32:51.210 align:middle line:84%
What do they need to do in
order to facilitate a deepening

00:32:51.210 --> 00:32:53.273 align:middle line:90%
in your relationship?

00:32:53.273 --> 00:32:55.440 align:middle line:84%
And it could be something
like, well, my sister just

00:32:55.440 --> 00:32:56.610 align:middle line:90%
needs to be vulnerable.

00:32:56.610 --> 00:33:00.180 align:middle line:84%
Stop having all the goddamn
answers and always being right.

00:33:00.180 --> 00:33:02.130 align:middle line:84%
And then, of course,
I twist it and I go,

00:33:02.130 --> 00:33:07.090 align:middle line:84%
are you doing the thing that
you want from them back?

00:33:07.090 --> 00:33:11.950 align:middle line:84%
And if people are honest,
typically the answer is no.

00:33:11.950 --> 00:33:16.322 align:middle line:84%
Forgiveness is a wonderful
gift to give to somebody else,

00:33:16.322 --> 00:33:18.280 align:middle line:84%
but forgiveness is probably
one of the greatest

00:33:18.280 --> 00:33:19.810 align:middle line:90%
gifts you can give to yourself.

00:33:19.810 --> 00:33:22.510 align:middle line:84%
If you're holding a
grudge to somebody else,

00:33:22.510 --> 00:33:25.490 align:middle line:84%
you're paying the
price every single day.

00:33:25.490 --> 00:33:26.290 align:middle line:90%
Go first.

00:33:26.290 --> 00:33:28.340 align:middle line:90%
What have you got to lose?

00:33:28.340 --> 00:33:29.140 align:middle line:90%
Say sorry.

00:33:29.140 --> 00:33:29.830 align:middle line:90%
Say, I'm wrong.

00:33:29.830 --> 00:33:30.630 align:middle line:90%
Say, I'm scared.

00:33:30.630 --> 00:33:31.510 align:middle line:90%
Say, I don't know.

00:33:31.510 --> 00:33:34.300 align:middle line:84%
The three most beautiful
words that every parent

00:33:34.300 --> 00:33:38.180 align:middle line:84%
should have every single day
in front of their children.

00:33:38.180 --> 00:33:39.050 align:middle line:90%
I don't know, son.

00:33:39.050 --> 00:33:43.060 align:middle line:90%


00:33:43.060 --> 00:33:45.610 align:middle line:84%
Allow your kids to see
your humanity so they

00:33:45.610 --> 00:33:47.110 align:middle line:90%
begin to recognize their own.

00:33:47.110 --> 00:33:55.720 align:middle line:90%


00:33:55.720 --> 00:34:01.840 align:middle line:84%
>> You ran a talk, One Last
Talk recently in prison.

00:34:01.840 --> 00:34:06.160 align:middle line:84%
I think that's
amazing, first of all.

00:34:06.160 --> 00:34:09.880 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell me about how hard
it was to make that happen?

00:34:09.880 --> 00:34:15.020 align:middle line:84%
And then talk me through some of
the eventual outcomes of that,

00:34:15.020 --> 00:34:18.870 align:middle line:84%
because I found that
quite an impactful story.

00:34:18.870 --> 00:34:19.760 align:middle line:90%
[SIGH]

00:34:19.760 --> 00:34:24.659 align:middle line:84%
>> So it started with asking
a man who has been released,

00:34:24.659 --> 00:34:27.500 align:middle line:84%
who committed murder, to stand
on stage and share his one last

00:34:27.500 --> 00:34:28.300 align:middle line:90%
talk.

00:34:28.300 --> 00:34:30.110 align:middle line:90%
And that happened in Boulder.

00:34:30.110 --> 00:34:32.900 align:middle line:84%
And when you do a One Last
Talk, you don't go on the stage

00:34:32.900 --> 00:34:34.980 align:middle line:84%
and say, hi, my name
is, I'm glad to be here,

00:34:34.980 --> 00:34:36.272 align:middle line:90%
thanks for-- any of that stuff.

00:34:36.272 --> 00:34:40.340 align:middle line:84%
You just walk out and
you begin your story.

00:34:40.340 --> 00:34:42.469 align:middle line:84%
And he walked out,
and his opening line

00:34:42.469 --> 00:34:46.190 align:middle line:84%
was something along the lines
of, on September 5, 1999,

00:34:46.190 --> 00:34:49.969 align:middle line:84%
I shot and killed--
and he named the man.

00:34:49.969 --> 00:34:52.877 align:middle line:84%
And then he said, and I tried to
shoot and kill three other men.

00:34:52.877 --> 00:34:53.960 align:middle line:90%
That was his opening line.

00:34:53.960 --> 00:34:57.980 align:middle line:10%
You could feel the
energy shift in the room.

00:34:57.980 --> 00:34:59.240 align:middle line:90%
You could feel the judgment.

00:34:59.240 --> 00:35:01.637 align:middle line:84%
I could feel the eyes
in the back of my head.

00:35:01.637 --> 00:35:03.470 align:middle line:84%
And he walked through
his story and he says,

00:35:03.470 --> 00:35:05.060 align:middle line:84%
I'm not here to
justify what I did.

00:35:05.060 --> 00:35:06.740 align:middle line:84%
I'm not here to say,
here's my story.

00:35:06.740 --> 00:35:07.850 align:middle line:90%
This is why I did it.

00:35:07.850 --> 00:35:08.720 align:middle line:90%
That's up to you.

00:35:08.720 --> 00:35:11.000 align:middle line:10%
I have to live with my
consequences of something

00:35:11.000 --> 00:35:13.310 align:middle line:10%
that I did that I'm
deeply ashamed of.

00:35:13.310 --> 00:35:15.500 align:middle line:84%
But I've been asked here
today to share my story,

00:35:15.500 --> 00:35:17.080 align:middle line:90%
and that's what I'm going to do.

00:35:17.080 --> 00:35:18.080 align:middle line:90%
And he shared his story.

00:35:18.080 --> 00:35:21.080 align:middle line:84%
And at the end of
the talk, he said,

00:35:21.080 --> 00:35:24.230 align:middle line:84%
I wrote a letter that never went
to the mother of the victim.

00:35:24.230 --> 00:35:25.400 align:middle line:90%
They couldn't find her.

00:35:25.400 --> 00:35:26.900 align:middle line:10%
And he reached into
his back pocket,

00:35:26.900 --> 00:35:29.960 align:middle line:10%
and he opened up the letter,
and he read the letter

00:35:29.960 --> 00:35:33.950 align:middle line:10%
to the mother of the
man that he shot.

00:35:33.950 --> 00:35:36.830 align:middle line:10%
It was one of the most
extraordinary things I've ever

00:35:36.830 --> 00:35:38.240 align:middle line:10%
experienced in my life.

00:35:38.240 --> 00:35:40.170 align:middle line:10%
And what came next was
more extraordinary.

00:35:40.170 --> 00:35:42.273 align:middle line:10%
We had 120 people
or so in the room.

00:35:42.273 --> 00:35:43.940 align:middle line:84%
He got an overwhelming
standing ovation.

00:35:43.940 --> 00:35:45.357 align:middle line:84%
And one man took
the mic and said,

00:35:45.357 --> 00:35:48.056 align:middle line:84%
can I just apologize
for judging you?

00:35:48.056 --> 00:35:51.370 align:middle line:84%
And personally, the thing that
moved me the most is my then

00:35:51.370 --> 00:35:52.950 align:middle line:90%
nine-year-old boy--

00:35:52.950 --> 00:35:55.120 align:middle line:84%
and I never do one of
these, go and kiss granny

00:35:55.120 --> 00:35:58.630 align:middle line:84%
or go and give your man a hug
or go and tell him he's great.

00:35:58.630 --> 00:36:00.940 align:middle line:84%
When Quan got off the
stage, my nine-year-old son

00:36:00.940 --> 00:36:03.040 align:middle line:84%
walked up, put his
arms around him,

00:36:03.040 --> 00:36:07.710 align:middle line:84%
hugged him, held it, and
said, I loved your talk.

00:36:07.710 --> 00:36:12.490 align:middle line:84%
And Quan looked at me
and just broke down.

00:36:12.490 --> 00:36:14.880 align:middle line:84%
And that was the
gateway into prison.

00:36:14.880 --> 00:36:17.910 align:middle line:10%
That was the opportunity to
work with an organization

00:36:17.910 --> 00:36:21.750 align:middle line:10%
to get us into the prison,
and to bring an audience

00:36:21.750 --> 00:36:24.362 align:middle line:10%
and to put six men
on the stage to share

00:36:24.362 --> 00:36:26.820 align:middle line:10%
their one last talks, five of
which I believe had committed

00:36:26.820 --> 00:36:29.220 align:middle line:10%
murder, are serving time
for committing murder,

00:36:29.220 --> 00:36:31.680 align:middle line:10%
and one was a sex offender.

00:36:31.680 --> 00:36:35.400 align:middle line:84%
And what was so extraordinary
about the sex offender was

00:36:35.400 --> 00:36:37.230 align:middle line:90%
he was the last speaker.

00:36:37.230 --> 00:36:39.690 align:middle line:84%
I've almost died, very
close to death twice,

00:36:39.690 --> 00:36:41.640 align:middle line:84%
and yet I have never
seen another human

00:36:41.640 --> 00:36:43.650 align:middle line:90%
being more scared in my life.

00:36:43.650 --> 00:36:47.220 align:middle line:10%
I thought I understood
fear and scaredness

00:36:47.220 --> 00:36:50.028 align:middle line:10%
until I looked at this
man as he began his talk.

00:36:50.028 --> 00:36:51.570 align:middle line:84%
And I stood up and
I walked up to him

00:36:51.570 --> 00:36:53.250 align:middle line:90%
and I said, are you afraid?

00:36:53.250 --> 00:36:56.070 align:middle line:90%
And he goes, I'm beyond afraid.

00:36:56.070 --> 00:36:58.980 align:middle line:10%
It's the first time he's
ever spoken about his story

00:36:58.980 --> 00:37:01.363 align:middle line:10%
and who he was as a person.

00:37:01.363 --> 00:37:03.030 align:middle line:84%
And when you do that
in a prison system,

00:37:03.030 --> 00:37:04.738 align:middle line:84%
there's a very strong
likelihood that you

00:37:04.738 --> 00:37:07.770 align:middle line:90%
could be beaten up or killed.

00:37:07.770 --> 00:37:10.513 align:middle line:84%
But that's not what
he was afraid of.

00:37:10.513 --> 00:37:11.930 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't afraid
of being stabbed.

00:37:11.930 --> 00:37:14.222 align:middle line:84%
He wasn't afraid of getting
the shit kicked out of him.

00:37:14.222 --> 00:37:18.260 align:middle line:84%
He was so afraid of
sharing all of who he is.

00:37:18.260 --> 00:37:22.220 align:middle line:84%
He was afraid of
not being accepted.

00:37:22.220 --> 00:37:24.560 align:middle line:84%
He was afraid and
not being seen.

00:37:24.560 --> 00:37:27.840 align:middle line:84%
And he knows what that's like,
because that is his whole life.

00:37:27.840 --> 00:37:30.200 align:middle line:84%
He went on to describe
one part of a story

00:37:30.200 --> 00:37:33.320 align:middle line:84%
that he was raped himself
every single day for six months

00:37:33.320 --> 00:37:35.835 align:middle line:90%
by his own father.

00:37:35.835 --> 00:37:37.460 align:middle line:84%
And what was the most
astonishing piece

00:37:37.460 --> 00:37:41.150 align:middle line:84%
was the inmates stood
up, bawling, crying,

00:37:41.150 --> 00:37:42.440 align:middle line:90%
went up and hugged him.

00:37:42.440 --> 00:37:43.670 align:middle line:90%
Said, I've got your back.

00:37:43.670 --> 00:37:44.630 align:middle line:90%
I didn't realize.

00:37:44.630 --> 00:37:45.890 align:middle line:90%
I was judging you.

00:37:45.890 --> 00:37:48.560 align:middle line:10%
And three women
who we invited in--

00:37:48.560 --> 00:37:53.030 align:middle line:10%
my wife included-- had been
raped, one woman very viciously

00:37:53.030 --> 00:37:55.760 align:middle line:10%
over multiple periods of time.

00:37:55.760 --> 00:37:58.830 align:middle line:84%
And each of them went
up and embraced him.

00:37:58.830 --> 00:38:01.020 align:middle line:84%
But where the wheels come
off for me emotionally

00:38:01.020 --> 00:38:03.840 align:middle line:84%
was the last place
where the woman who'd

00:38:03.840 --> 00:38:06.390 align:middle line:84%
gone through the most sexual
abuse turned to her husband

00:38:06.390 --> 00:38:08.663 align:middle line:84%
and she said, I don't
want him to leave.

00:38:08.663 --> 00:38:10.330 align:middle line:84%
And he goes, what are
you talking about?

00:38:10.330 --> 00:38:11.440 align:middle line:84%
She says, I don't
want him to leave.

00:38:11.440 --> 00:38:13.440 align:middle line:84%
I don't want him to go
back into the population.

00:38:13.440 --> 00:38:15.450 align:middle line:90%
I want to protect him.

00:38:15.450 --> 00:38:16.450 align:middle line:90%
I want to keep him safe.

00:38:16.450 --> 00:38:19.060 align:middle line:90%


00:38:19.060 --> 00:38:20.830 align:middle line:84%
And the healing that
happened in that room

00:38:20.830 --> 00:38:25.090 align:middle line:84%
is beyond anything I have
ever imagined in my life.

00:38:25.090 --> 00:38:28.077 align:middle line:84%
I never imagined I would be
a tiny part of something that

00:38:28.077 --> 00:38:29.910 align:middle line:84%
could help create that
or bring that to you.

00:38:29.910 --> 00:38:33.750 align:middle line:84%
I never imagined I'd sit in
a room and experience that.

00:38:33.750 --> 00:38:36.302 align:middle line:84%
I've never experienced healing
in my life like that day.

00:38:36.302 --> 00:38:38.260 align:middle line:84%
And my own wife said to
me afterward, she says,

00:38:38.260 --> 00:38:39.770 align:middle line:90%
I finally get it.

00:38:39.770 --> 00:38:41.400 align:middle line:84%
What happened to
me wasn't about me,

00:38:41.400 --> 00:38:44.490 align:middle line:84%
and yet that's what I've been
holding for the last 20 years.

00:38:44.490 --> 00:38:47.200 align:middle line:84%
It was about all what
was going on for them.

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:49.890 align:middle line:84%
And she was able to create
separation for the first time

00:38:49.890 --> 00:38:50.690 align:middle line:90%
ever.

00:38:50.690 --> 00:38:54.890 align:middle line:90%


00:38:54.890 --> 00:39:00.100 align:middle line:84%
And when I look at that, when
I think about One Last Talk,

00:39:00.100 --> 00:39:01.360 align:middle line:90%
it's bigger than me.

00:39:01.360 --> 00:39:02.755 align:middle line:90%
It's more important than me.

00:39:02.755 --> 00:39:04.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's something that
I don't feel I have--

00:39:04.630 --> 00:39:06.932 align:middle line:84%
I feel as if I have
a moral obligation

00:39:06.932 --> 00:39:08.640 align:middle line:84%
to bring that to the
world, because there

00:39:08.640 --> 00:39:09.940 align:middle line:84%
is nothing I have
experienced that it

00:39:09.940 --> 00:39:12.310 align:middle line:84%
creates healing and connection,
and therefore eradicates

00:39:12.310 --> 00:39:13.268 align:middle line:90%
loneliness.

00:39:13.268 --> 00:39:17.660 align:middle line:90%


00:39:17.660 --> 00:39:24.100 align:middle line:84%
>> This concept of separating
the person from the artifact,

00:39:24.100 --> 00:39:26.680 align:middle line:84%
or at least not judging
or blaming that person,

00:39:26.680 --> 00:39:31.690 align:middle line:84%
that seems to be the secret
to your ability to help people

00:39:31.690 --> 00:39:37.450 align:middle line:84%
break free from this fear and
pain that they're holding onto

00:39:37.450 --> 00:39:38.860 align:middle line:90%
in so many ways.

00:39:38.860 --> 00:39:41.530 align:middle line:84%
Is that the crux that you're
trying to lead people to?

00:39:41.530 --> 00:39:43.330 align:middle line:84%
Is that the opportunity
you see in this?

00:39:43.330 --> 00:39:44.980 align:middle line:84%
>> When it comes to
connecting with--

00:39:44.980 --> 00:39:47.050 align:middle line:84%
helping people connect,
because connection

00:39:47.050 --> 00:39:48.810 align:middle line:90%
is what it's all about for me.

00:39:48.810 --> 00:39:49.830 align:middle line:84%
You know, people think
it's about business.

00:39:49.830 --> 00:39:50.860 align:middle line:84%
It's about helping
people connect

00:39:50.860 --> 00:39:52.735 align:middle line:84%
to meaningful work,
meaningful relationships,

00:39:52.735 --> 00:39:54.152 align:middle line:84%
and a relationship
with themselves

00:39:54.152 --> 00:39:55.585 align:middle line:90%
that they're truly proud of.

00:39:55.585 --> 00:39:57.565 align:middle line:84%
And I remember one day
walking into a workshop,

00:39:57.565 --> 00:39:59.352 align:middle line:84%
and I don't know how
this lady did it.

00:39:59.352 --> 00:40:01.310 align:middle line:84%
There must have been 30
people at the workshop.

00:40:01.310 --> 00:40:02.810 align:middle line:10%
And by the time we
started, she must

00:40:02.810 --> 00:40:05.740 align:middle line:10%
have got around to everybody,
everybody in the room,

00:40:05.740 --> 00:40:08.200 align:middle line:10%
and shared her tragedy.

00:40:08.200 --> 00:40:10.780 align:middle line:84%
And her tragic story
was that her husband

00:40:10.780 --> 00:40:12.880 align:middle line:84%
cheated on her in
the most obnoxious,

00:40:12.880 --> 00:40:15.070 align:middle line:90%
horrendous, disgusting way.

00:40:15.070 --> 00:40:19.210 align:middle line:84%
And she managed to get to
every single person pretty much

00:40:19.210 --> 00:40:22.120 align:middle line:84%
in the room and
download this story

00:40:22.120 --> 00:40:23.800 align:middle line:84%
and receive the
type of attention

00:40:23.800 --> 00:40:25.342 align:middle line:90%
that she had been used to.

00:40:25.342 --> 00:40:26.800 align:middle line:84%
I walk in, and the
first question I

00:40:26.800 --> 00:40:30.590 align:middle line:84%
ask, intuitively, I just
said, so what brings you here?

00:40:30.590 --> 00:40:33.860 align:middle line:90%
Why are you here, really?

00:40:33.860 --> 00:40:36.230 align:middle line:84%
And she was-- and I said,
you're obviously eager to go.

00:40:36.230 --> 00:40:37.790 align:middle line:90%
And she goes, yeah.

00:40:37.790 --> 00:40:39.140 align:middle line:90%
My husband ripped my heart out.

00:40:39.140 --> 00:40:40.600 align:middle line:90%
My life has turned upside down.

00:40:40.600 --> 00:40:41.830 align:middle line:90%
I was blindsided.

00:40:41.830 --> 00:40:44.470 align:middle line:84%
This happened a year ago,
and no one saw it coming,

00:40:44.470 --> 00:40:47.378 align:middle line:90%
and my life is in turmoil.

00:40:47.378 --> 00:40:48.920 align:middle line:84%
And I said, you
didn't see it coming?

00:40:48.920 --> 00:40:49.310 align:middle line:90%
She goes, no.

00:40:49.310 --> 00:40:49.970 align:middle line:90%
I didn't see it coming.

00:40:49.970 --> 00:40:51.710 align:middle line:84%
You could feel the energy,
everyone in the room, go,

00:40:51.710 --> 00:40:53.570 align:middle line:84%
oh, god love her,
and everything else.

00:40:53.570 --> 00:40:57.370 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I don't
believe you for one second.

00:40:57.370 --> 00:40:59.080 align:middle line:90%
I'd never met her before.

00:40:59.080 --> 00:41:00.600 align:middle line:90%
She goes, excuse me?

00:41:00.600 --> 00:41:03.540 align:middle line:90%
I said, you are so smart.

00:41:03.540 --> 00:41:06.960 align:middle line:84%
You come across as
being so intuitive.

00:41:06.960 --> 00:41:09.800 align:middle line:84%
You're telling me you
did not see this coming?

00:41:09.800 --> 00:41:11.720 align:middle line:84%
You're telling me
you had no sense

00:41:11.720 --> 00:41:15.020 align:middle line:84%
that this possibility was
going to exist in your life?

00:41:15.020 --> 00:41:17.250 align:middle line:90%
I don't believe you.

00:41:17.250 --> 00:41:20.240 align:middle line:90%
And the anger emerged.

00:41:20.240 --> 00:41:21.140 align:middle line:90%
She was vibrating.

00:41:21.140 --> 00:41:23.840 align:middle line:84%
She wanted to rip my head off,
which is not uncommon sometimes

00:41:23.840 --> 00:41:25.040 align:middle line:90%
initially.

00:41:25.040 --> 00:41:27.553 align:middle line:84%
And I said, are you
angry right now?

00:41:27.553 --> 00:41:28.970 align:middle line:84%
She goes, no, no,
no, No, I'm not.

00:41:28.970 --> 00:41:29.770 align:middle line:90%
No, I'm not.

00:41:29.770 --> 00:41:32.860 align:middle line:84%
And she looked like she was
going to strangle somebody.

00:41:32.860 --> 00:41:36.120 align:middle line:84%
And I said, let's just name the
anger that's present, and let's

00:41:36.120 --> 00:41:40.490 align:middle line:84%
just drop just below that,
and let's see what emerges.

00:41:40.490 --> 00:41:44.430 align:middle line:84%
And her head drops, and she
shook and shook and shook.

00:41:44.430 --> 00:41:48.130 align:middle line:10%
And she lifted her face, and
the tears pouring down her face.

00:41:48.130 --> 00:41:51.140 align:middle line:84%
And she says, I knew
it the day I met him,

00:41:51.140 --> 00:41:53.030 align:middle line:84%
and I knew I shouldn't
marry him the day

00:41:53.030 --> 00:41:54.160 align:middle line:90%
I walked down the aisle.

00:41:54.160 --> 00:41:58.150 align:middle line:90%


00:41:58.150 --> 00:42:00.640 align:middle line:84%
People might say,
well, why would you

00:42:00.640 --> 00:42:01.820 align:middle line:90%
facilitate uncovering that?

00:42:01.820 --> 00:42:02.620 align:middle line:90%
I'll tell you why.

00:42:02.620 --> 00:42:04.480 align:middle line:90%
It's very simple.

00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:06.460 align:middle line:84%
So she never repeats
the same pattern again,

00:42:06.460 --> 00:42:08.290 align:middle line:84%
that she understands
her part in it.

00:42:08.290 --> 00:42:09.290 align:middle line:90%
Maybe he was an asshole.

00:42:09.290 --> 00:42:11.030 align:middle line:90%
Maybe he did something wrong.

00:42:11.030 --> 00:42:11.830 align:middle line:90%
But she knew it.

00:42:11.830 --> 00:42:13.455 align:middle line:84%
She picked the wrong
person because she

00:42:13.455 --> 00:42:15.730 align:middle line:84%
was so attached to
being in a relationship

00:42:15.730 --> 00:42:19.090 align:middle line:84%
that she chose to ignore the
red flags on the peripheral,

00:42:19.090 --> 00:42:21.850 align:middle line:84%
because she had her
eyes on the prize,

00:42:21.850 --> 00:42:23.560 align:middle line:84%
because she didn't
believe she could

00:42:23.560 --> 00:42:25.760 align:middle line:84%
be happy on her own
journey in this world,

00:42:25.760 --> 00:42:30.650 align:middle line:84%
that she needed somebody else
to validate and support her.

00:42:30.650 --> 00:42:35.740 align:middle line:84%
And now that she understands
that, she's aware of that,

00:42:35.740 --> 00:42:37.110 align:middle line:90%
she can forgive.

00:42:37.110 --> 00:42:38.940 align:middle line:90%
She can let go.

00:42:38.940 --> 00:42:40.920 align:middle line:84%
She can let go of
the charge, and even

00:42:40.920 --> 00:42:45.910 align:middle line:84%
get to the point to
forgive her ex and free

00:42:45.910 --> 00:42:49.150 align:middle line:84%
herself of the burden, and
allow love to come into her life

00:42:49.150 --> 00:42:51.072 align:middle line:84%
where perhaps there
was no space for it.

00:42:51.072 --> 00:42:55.140 align:middle line:90%


00:42:55.140 --> 00:42:59.920 align:middle line:84%
>> It seems a lot of your work
is based in vulnerability.

00:42:59.920 --> 00:43:04.990 align:middle line:84%
Is this a key element to
helping people unlock what

00:43:04.990 --> 00:43:06.730 align:middle line:90%
they're hiding?

00:43:06.730 --> 00:43:08.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Vulnerability to me
is just someone's truth.

00:43:08.890 --> 00:43:10.460 align:middle line:90%
It's just all of them.

00:43:10.460 --> 00:43:13.600 align:middle line:84%
And people work very,
very hard to present

00:43:13.600 --> 00:43:16.420 align:middle line:84%
the parts of themselves that
they want the world to see,

00:43:16.420 --> 00:43:19.390 align:middle line:84%
whether it's on Facebook or
whether it's in a room with me.

00:43:19.390 --> 00:43:21.996 align:middle line:90%
And I just--

00:43:21.996 --> 00:43:23.810 align:middle line:90%
I don't stop to think about it.

00:43:23.810 --> 00:43:27.910 align:middle line:84%
I just create a space to
allow people to show up

00:43:27.910 --> 00:43:29.520 align:middle line:90%
and to open up.

00:43:29.520 --> 00:43:32.390 align:middle line:84%
And you know, people
are running very fast,

00:43:32.390 --> 00:43:37.210 align:middle line:84%
people who are moving so
fast and so busy, just afraid

00:43:37.210 --> 00:43:39.790 align:middle line:84%
to stop and to
connect emotionally

00:43:39.790 --> 00:43:42.100 align:middle line:84%
with the very thing
they're avoiding.

00:43:42.100 --> 00:43:45.460 align:middle line:10%
I had a business owner
recently who has made it

00:43:45.460 --> 00:43:48.290 align:middle line:10%
multiple times over in
terms of financially.

00:43:48.290 --> 00:43:51.790 align:middle line:10%
And he just says, I
don't have any friends.

00:43:51.790 --> 00:43:53.710 align:middle line:90%
It's lonely.

00:43:53.710 --> 00:43:57.130 align:middle line:84%
And what he has done is he's
doubled down on the very place

00:43:57.130 --> 00:43:59.972 align:middle line:84%
that he feels that he's deriving
value, that he's presenting

00:43:59.972 --> 00:44:01.930 align:middle line:84%
value to the world, where
he gets significance,

00:44:01.930 --> 00:44:03.130 align:middle line:90%
and that's his work.

00:44:03.130 --> 00:44:06.810 align:middle line:10%
And that's why he has
become a workaholic.

00:44:06.810 --> 00:44:10.110 align:middle line:10%
And my job is to allow
him to get to the place

00:44:10.110 --> 00:44:14.310 align:middle line:10%
where he presents his truth,
and then we can build on that.

00:44:14.310 --> 00:44:16.860 align:middle line:84%
But unless that truth emerges,
if someone's hiding something

00:44:16.860 --> 00:44:19.415 align:middle line:84%
from themselves and therefore
me, I can't really help them.

00:44:19.415 --> 00:44:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And all I'm asking you to
do is to show up and show

00:44:21.540 --> 00:44:24.390 align:middle line:84%
me all of you, and I promise
you I will never judge you.

00:44:24.390 --> 00:44:26.852 align:middle line:90%


00:44:26.852 --> 00:44:29.310 align:middle line:84%
>> How can people really not
know they're hiding something,

00:44:29.310 --> 00:44:30.110 align:middle line:90%
though?

00:44:30.110 --> 00:44:32.760 align:middle line:84%
Because it's so insidious
the ways that we go out

00:44:32.760 --> 00:44:34.320 align:middle line:84%
into the world
and we work and we

00:44:34.320 --> 00:44:35.880 align:middle line:90%
prove our sense of self-worth.

00:44:35.880 --> 00:44:36.840 align:middle line:84%
And we're doing
this whole thing,

00:44:36.840 --> 00:44:38.495 align:middle line:84%
we're putting on
these masks every day.

00:44:38.495 --> 00:44:40.620 align:middle line:84%
These masks, these new
masks about who we should be

00:44:40.620 --> 00:44:42.600 align:middle line:90%
or what I'm going to do next.

00:44:42.600 --> 00:44:46.740 align:middle line:84%
And then how do we even know
who our real self is anymore?

00:44:46.740 --> 00:44:49.320 align:middle line:90%
How do we-- like, really.

00:44:49.320 --> 00:44:50.130 align:middle line:90%
How do we?

00:44:50.130 --> 00:44:51.900 align:middle line:84%
How do we understand
that part of us

00:44:51.900 --> 00:44:54.370 align:middle line:84%
that's eternal, that's always
us, that's always been us?

00:44:54.370 --> 00:44:55.590 align:middle line:90%
That's tricky work.

00:44:55.590 --> 00:45:00.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think the key to
that is letting go of the things

00:45:00.750 --> 00:45:03.100 align:middle line:84%
that we hold on to that
are part of our identity.

00:45:03.100 --> 00:45:03.900 align:middle line:90%
And that scares us.

00:45:03.900 --> 00:45:06.785 align:middle line:84%
It's like not being
a very strong swimmer

00:45:06.785 --> 00:45:08.160 align:middle line:84%
and then asking
someone to let go

00:45:08.160 --> 00:45:09.950 align:middle line:84%
of the bar at the
side of the pool.

00:45:09.950 --> 00:45:12.450 align:middle line:84%
And they feel very vulnerable,
and they feel out of control.

00:45:12.450 --> 00:45:16.110 align:middle line:84%
And control is this new,
emerging obsession with people.

00:45:16.110 --> 00:45:17.820 align:middle line:84%
If I'm in control,
then I'm safe.

00:45:17.820 --> 00:45:21.210 align:middle line:84%
And of course, that's
a complete illusion.

00:45:21.210 --> 00:45:24.445 align:middle line:84%
And I look back even at my own
life and I think to myself,

00:45:24.445 --> 00:45:26.320 align:middle line:84%
no one asked me, did I
want to be a Catholic?

00:45:26.320 --> 00:45:27.120 align:middle line:90%
I was told I was a Catholic.

00:45:27.120 --> 00:45:28.320 align:middle line:84%
No one asked me, do I
want to be Christian?

00:45:28.320 --> 00:45:29.190 align:middle line:90%
I was told I was a Christian.

00:45:29.190 --> 00:45:30.500 align:middle line:84%
No one asked me, do I
want to go to school?

00:45:30.500 --> 00:45:31.590 align:middle line:90%
I was told to go to school.

00:45:31.590 --> 00:45:33.465 align:middle line:84%
No one asked me, did I
want to learn algebra?

00:45:33.465 --> 00:45:35.250 align:middle line:90%
I was told you learn it.

00:45:35.250 --> 00:45:36.060 align:middle line:90%
That was useful.

00:45:36.060 --> 00:45:36.860 align:middle line:90%
Not.

00:45:36.860 --> 00:45:38.970 align:middle line:90%


00:45:38.970 --> 00:45:41.945 align:middle line:84%
We have to look at
our lives in a very--

00:45:41.945 --> 00:45:43.320 align:middle line:84%
one of the things
that's missing,

00:45:43.320 --> 00:45:47.220 align:middle line:84%
James, when it comes
to exploration of self,

00:45:47.220 --> 00:45:49.620 align:middle line:84%
what's completely missing
in so many people's lives

00:45:49.620 --> 00:45:51.750 align:middle line:90%
is curiosity.

00:45:51.750 --> 00:45:54.950 align:middle line:84%
I sat in front of
a couple one day.

00:45:54.950 --> 00:45:57.770 align:middle line:84%
I was asking them to describe
where they would love to live,

00:45:57.770 --> 00:45:59.130 align:middle line:84%
because they were on
polar different pages.

00:45:59.130 --> 00:46:00.547 align:middle line:84%
At least that's
what they thought.

00:46:00.547 --> 00:46:03.200 align:middle line:84%
But 99.9% of couples want
exactly the same thing

00:46:03.200 --> 00:46:05.783 align:middle line:84%
in my experience, yet we just
speak a different language.

00:46:05.783 --> 00:46:06.950 align:middle line:90%
And I asked them to connect.

00:46:06.950 --> 00:46:08.840 align:middle line:84%
And they ultimately
came to this conclusion

00:46:08.840 --> 00:46:11.090 align:middle line:84%
that they both
wanted to move home

00:46:11.090 --> 00:46:13.490 align:middle line:84%
to where they were
both born in BC

00:46:13.490 --> 00:46:15.370 align:middle line:90%
up in the mountains in Kelowna.

00:46:15.370 --> 00:46:17.210 align:middle line:84%
But their faces
were contracting,

00:46:17.210 --> 00:46:18.940 align:middle line:90%
and they were like, oh, jeez.

00:46:18.940 --> 00:46:19.910 align:middle line:90%
You know, it was hard.

00:46:19.910 --> 00:46:22.970 align:middle line:84%
And you know, making it complex
and making it challenging.

00:46:22.970 --> 00:46:25.348 align:middle line:84%
And I just said, guys,
what are you-- stop.

00:46:25.348 --> 00:46:27.140 align:middle line:84%
And they looked at me,
and they said, what?

00:46:27.140 --> 00:46:29.880 align:middle line:84%
I said, if we had a guy standing
outside the door looking in

00:46:29.880 --> 00:46:31.610 align:middle line:84%
through the window
and he couldn't

00:46:31.610 --> 00:46:34.880 align:middle line:84%
hear what you were saying
about re-imagining your future

00:46:34.880 --> 00:46:37.220 align:middle line:84%
and moving to a place
that nurtures you,

00:46:37.220 --> 00:46:39.320 align:middle line:84%
and he just had to look
at your body language

00:46:39.320 --> 00:46:41.610 align:middle line:84%
and he had to assess what
you were talking about,

00:46:41.610 --> 00:46:43.985 align:middle line:84%
he'd probably come and go,
is she dying of cancer,

00:46:43.985 --> 00:46:45.840 align:middle line:84%
or have they both got
six months to live?

00:46:45.840 --> 00:46:47.570 align:middle line:90%
Which is it?

00:46:47.570 --> 00:46:51.230 align:middle line:84%
We make this shit so
complex, and it is so simple.

00:46:51.230 --> 00:46:54.050 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things I love
to invite and challenge people

00:46:54.050 --> 00:46:57.650 align:middle line:84%
to do is act upon what we know
as opposed to what we do not.

00:46:57.650 --> 00:47:01.890 align:middle line:84%
So if I'm living in Boulder,
Colorado, and I don't like it,

00:47:01.890 --> 00:47:03.510 align:middle line:84%
the biggest obstacle
I'll put my way

00:47:03.510 --> 00:47:06.510 align:middle line:84%
is, but I don't know
where I do like, James.

00:47:06.510 --> 00:47:09.660 align:middle line:90%
I don't know where is next.

00:47:09.660 --> 00:47:14.050 align:middle line:84%
My answer is if it's
not Boulder, anywhere.

00:47:14.050 --> 00:47:16.260 align:middle line:10%
But what if I move to
Seattle and I don't like it?

00:47:16.260 --> 00:47:18.690 align:middle line:90%
You move again.

00:47:18.690 --> 00:47:21.570 align:middle line:84%
We put so much emphasis
on the next move

00:47:21.570 --> 00:47:25.830 align:middle line:84%
that it stifles us
from doing anything.

00:47:25.830 --> 00:47:28.247 align:middle line:84%
People come to me for clarity
about where they should move

00:47:28.247 --> 00:47:29.663 align:middle line:84%
and businesses
they should set up.

00:47:29.663 --> 00:47:30.840 align:middle line:90%
I go, let's look at reality.

00:47:30.840 --> 00:47:32.280 align:middle line:84%
Let's look at your
current reality.

00:47:32.280 --> 00:47:33.080 align:middle line:90%
What is working?

00:47:33.080 --> 00:47:34.955 align:middle line:90%
And let's start there.

00:47:34.955 --> 00:47:36.330 align:middle line:84%
That's the simple
place to start.

00:47:36.330 --> 00:47:37.950 align:middle line:90%


00:47:37.950 --> 00:47:40.450 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the common threads
that you've had throughout this

00:47:40.450 --> 00:47:42.825 align:middle line:84%
conversation we've had-- and
it's been very enlightening,

00:47:42.825 --> 00:47:48.100 align:middle line:84%
thank you-- is this idea that
we are more disconnected now

00:47:48.100 --> 00:47:50.680 align:middle line:84%
despite being in a world
that's more connected than ever

00:47:50.680 --> 00:47:52.000 align:middle line:90%
before.

00:47:52.000 --> 00:47:54.910 align:middle line:84%
And ultimately, I think,
if I'm correct here,

00:47:54.910 --> 00:47:57.160 align:middle line:84%
that's the core
wound you're trying

00:47:57.160 --> 00:47:59.870 align:middle line:84%
to heal in trying to prove
that we are connected,

00:47:59.870 --> 00:48:00.670 align:middle line:90%
we are related.

00:48:00.670 --> 00:48:04.300 align:middle line:84%
And we've been taught in these
ideals of the evolution theory

00:48:04.300 --> 00:48:06.040 align:middle line:90%
that it's all about competition.

00:48:06.040 --> 00:48:07.830 align:middle line:84%
And then science is
now proving that, no.

00:48:07.830 --> 00:48:10.247 align:middle line:84%
The big trees don't crowd the
light from the little trees.

00:48:10.247 --> 00:48:13.900 align:middle line:84%
They give nutrients via the
mycelium and via the mushrooms

00:48:13.900 --> 00:48:16.120 align:middle line:84%
they grow and the fungi
underneath the soil

00:48:16.120 --> 00:48:17.208 align:middle line:90%
to support those trees.

00:48:17.208 --> 00:48:19.000 align:middle line:84%
And in certain other
times, the small trees

00:48:19.000 --> 00:48:20.740 align:middle line:90%
support the big trees.

00:48:20.740 --> 00:48:22.780 align:middle line:84%
There is an enormous
web of cooperation

00:48:22.780 --> 00:48:24.070 align:middle line:90%
that happens in the world.

00:48:24.070 --> 00:48:25.780 align:middle line:84%
And my question to
you is, how do you

00:48:25.780 --> 00:48:29.590 align:middle line:84%
think we start to heal these
big problems, the disconnect,

00:48:29.590 --> 00:48:32.520 align:middle line:84%
the emotional trauma,
the locking it all down,

00:48:32.520 --> 00:48:35.590 align:middle line:84%
the repeating it again,
generation after generation?

00:48:35.590 --> 00:48:38.230 align:middle line:84%
How do we start to solve some
of these huge problems that

00:48:38.230 --> 00:48:40.540 align:middle line:84%
could really, if we
did solve them, help

00:48:40.540 --> 00:48:43.757 align:middle line:84%
to unlock possibilities
that could potentially

00:48:43.757 --> 00:48:46.090 align:middle line:84%
solve the biggest problems
that we face on planet Earth,

00:48:46.090 --> 00:48:47.900 align:middle line:90%
I think?

00:48:47.900 --> 00:48:51.610 align:middle line:84%
>> I mean, obviously I'm biased,
and obviously I'm connected

00:48:51.610 --> 00:48:53.727 align:middle line:84%
to what we're doing
through One Last Talk.

00:48:53.727 --> 00:48:55.810 align:middle line:84%
I'm not saying it's the
answer, but it's certainly

00:48:55.810 --> 00:48:57.950 align:middle line:90%
our way of doing this.

00:48:57.950 --> 00:49:01.660 align:middle line:84%
Another avenue for this
is through the lens

00:49:01.660 --> 00:49:04.870 align:middle line:84%
of organizations
and corporations.

00:49:04.870 --> 00:49:08.020 align:middle line:84%
And in many cases, you've got
so many millions of people

00:49:08.020 --> 00:49:10.930 align:middle line:84%
who get up in the morning, go
to a community or an office

00:49:10.930 --> 00:49:13.870 align:middle line:84%
or a job or a business,
and then they come home,

00:49:13.870 --> 00:49:16.245 align:middle line:84%
they watch Netflix, they go
to sleep, or they watch FMTV.

00:49:16.245 --> 00:49:18.787 align:middle line:84%
And they go to sleep, and they
wake up the following morning.

00:49:18.787 --> 00:49:19.990 align:middle line:90%
It's rinse and repeat.

00:49:19.990 --> 00:49:21.740 align:middle line:84%
And for many of those,
their community,

00:49:21.740 --> 00:49:24.190 align:middle line:84%
their village is
the place they work.

00:49:24.190 --> 00:49:26.860 align:middle line:84%
And we hear all the
time around culture.

00:49:26.860 --> 00:49:29.670 align:middle line:84%
You know, this culture and
that culture and whatever.

00:49:29.670 --> 00:49:32.740 align:middle line:90%
And it's getting so noisy.

00:49:32.740 --> 00:49:35.585 align:middle line:84%
To me, culture is built on
nothing other than trust.

00:49:35.585 --> 00:49:37.960 align:middle line:84%
And I think if you can create
an environment where people

00:49:37.960 --> 00:49:40.293 align:middle line:84%
can understand why they don't
trust themselves and begin

00:49:40.293 --> 00:49:42.793 align:middle line:84%
to reconcile that, then they
start to trust their intuition.

00:49:42.793 --> 00:49:44.376 align:middle line:84%
Then they start to
trust their bodies.

00:49:44.376 --> 00:49:45.940 align:middle line:10%
Then they start to
trust each other.

00:49:45.940 --> 00:49:48.870 align:middle line:84%
To me, it's all built on
this sense of trust inside.

00:49:48.870 --> 00:49:50.470 align:middle line:84%
And again, someone
said, you know,

00:49:50.470 --> 00:49:53.033 align:middle line:84%
companies are never going to
allow One Last Talk to happen

00:49:53.033 --> 00:49:53.950 align:middle line:90%
in their organization.

00:49:53.950 --> 00:49:55.200 align:middle line:90%
It's just not going to happen.

00:49:55.200 --> 00:49:57.533 align:middle line:84%
They're not going to create
that sense of vulnerability.

00:49:57.533 --> 00:50:00.180 align:middle line:84%
And there's a theory called
the self-determination theory.

00:50:00.180 --> 00:50:01.722 align:middle line:10%
I don't know if
you've read about it.

00:50:01.722 --> 00:50:04.060 align:middle line:10%
And it cites after
massive research

00:50:04.060 --> 00:50:06.700 align:middle line:10%
that human beings deeply
desire three things.

00:50:06.700 --> 00:50:09.550 align:middle line:84%
They want to feel
competent at what they do,

00:50:09.550 --> 00:50:11.680 align:middle line:84%
they want to feel authentic
in their own lives,

00:50:11.680 --> 00:50:14.550 align:middle line:90%
and they want to feel connected.

00:50:14.550 --> 00:50:18.153 align:middle line:84%
And we're now going into
multiple organizations,

00:50:18.153 --> 00:50:20.070 align:middle line:84%
and we're creating an
environment where people

00:50:20.070 --> 00:50:23.070 align:middle line:84%
stand up and share a very
vulnerable part of themselves

00:50:23.070 --> 00:50:26.840 align:middle line:84%
to a community of people
that they work with.

00:50:26.840 --> 00:50:29.190 align:middle line:84%
And what's happening,
which I knew

00:50:29.190 --> 00:50:33.180 align:middle line:84%
intuitively was going to happen,
but now we have the proof,

00:50:33.180 --> 00:50:35.460 align:middle line:84%
is that connection
goes through the roof.

00:50:35.460 --> 00:50:36.960 align:middle line:90%
Attrition goes down.

00:50:36.960 --> 00:50:38.670 align:middle line:90%
Loyalty starts to happen.

00:50:38.670 --> 00:50:41.180 align:middle line:90%
This sense of, I have your back.

00:50:41.180 --> 00:50:44.610 align:middle line:84%
And this sense of
belonging and connection

00:50:44.610 --> 00:50:47.462 align:middle line:84%
is emerging within
cultures and companies.

00:50:47.462 --> 00:50:49.420 align:middle line:10%
So I don't know how we
do it on a global scale,

00:50:49.420 --> 00:50:51.900 align:middle line:10%
but I do know this,
is that we've all

00:50:51.900 --> 00:50:54.480 align:middle line:10%
got to take some degree
of responsibility for it.

00:50:54.480 --> 00:50:56.940 align:middle line:84%
I think I have a moral
obligation as a father

00:50:56.940 --> 00:50:59.550 align:middle line:84%
to work on my own
shit, even the stuff I

00:50:59.550 --> 00:51:01.410 align:middle line:90%
don't know that's there.

00:51:01.410 --> 00:51:04.540 align:middle line:84%
And I trust that by
doing that, my kids are

00:51:04.540 --> 00:51:05.790 align:middle line:90%
going to be in a better place.

00:51:05.790 --> 00:51:07.707 align:middle line:84%
But the one thing I'd
add to that is something

00:51:07.707 --> 00:51:11.730 align:middle line:84%
that I feel has worked extremely
well for us is recognize,

00:51:11.730 --> 00:51:15.012 align:middle line:84%
no matter what I do, I'm
going to mess my kids up.

00:51:15.012 --> 00:51:17.220 align:middle line:84%
No matter how good a parent--
if I hug them too much,

00:51:17.220 --> 00:51:17.940 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to mess them up.

00:51:17.940 --> 00:51:20.270 align:middle line:84%
If I never hug them at all,
I'm going to mess them up.

00:51:20.270 --> 00:51:22.710 align:middle line:84%
And what I mean by
that is I'm never

00:51:22.710 --> 00:51:24.840 align:middle line:84%
going to give up on
my kids, but maybe I

00:51:24.840 --> 00:51:26.940 align:middle line:84%
can let them go a
little bit and not

00:51:26.940 --> 00:51:30.270 align:middle line:90%
need to be the perfect father.

00:51:30.270 --> 00:51:34.020 align:middle line:10%
And that has given me a
degree of peace to give myself

00:51:34.020 --> 00:51:37.920 align:middle line:10%
a break when I lose my temper
or I have a short or I'm this

00:51:37.920 --> 00:51:39.630 align:middle line:10%
or I let myself
down, is that I don't

00:51:39.630 --> 00:51:41.730 align:middle line:10%
turn into this spiral
which takes me a week

00:51:41.730 --> 00:51:42.870 align:middle line:10%
to get back out of.

00:51:42.870 --> 00:51:45.140 align:middle line:84%
I forgive myself, I
name it, I apologize.

00:51:45.140 --> 00:51:45.940 align:middle line:90%
Let's move on.

00:51:45.940 --> 00:51:50.350 align:middle line:90%


00:51:50.350 --> 00:51:53.530 align:middle line:84%
>> And kids always seem to
forget and then forgive.

00:51:53.530 --> 00:51:54.460 align:middle line:90%
They do.

00:51:54.460 --> 00:51:55.510 align:middle line:90%
I've noticed that.

00:51:55.510 --> 00:51:57.520 align:middle line:84%
In my worst moments,
I feel bad, and I

00:51:57.520 --> 00:52:00.430 align:middle line:84%
feel like I've caused
irreparable damage.

00:52:00.430 --> 00:52:03.790 align:middle line:84%
And in the morning, there is
a hug and a kiss and a look.

00:52:03.790 --> 00:52:04.640 align:middle line:90%
Hey, I love you.

00:52:04.640 --> 00:52:05.440 align:middle line:90%
How you doing?

00:52:05.440 --> 00:52:06.130 align:middle line:90%
And it's like, wow.

00:52:06.130 --> 00:52:06.940 align:middle line:90%
You forgive me?

00:52:06.940 --> 00:52:07.740 align:middle line:90%
Oh my goodness.

00:52:07.740 --> 00:52:10.045 align:middle line:90%
What another opportunity, right?

00:52:10.045 --> 00:52:14.440 align:middle line:10%
>> I asked a man recently
to share his One Last Talk

00:52:14.440 --> 00:52:16.170 align:middle line:10%
on stage.

00:52:16.170 --> 00:52:19.890 align:middle line:10%
And he shared for the first
time ever-- he wasn't even sure

00:52:19.890 --> 00:52:20.880 align:middle line:10%
why he was sharing it.

00:52:20.880 --> 00:52:23.047 align:middle line:84%
And one of the biggest
challenges with One Last Talk

00:52:23.047 --> 00:52:25.800 align:middle line:84%
or anything else is
that I think deep down,

00:52:25.800 --> 00:52:27.120 align:middle line:90%
we all want to make an impact.

00:52:27.120 --> 00:52:32.200 align:middle line:84%
But the challenge is we all
want to look good doing it.

00:52:32.200 --> 00:52:35.033 align:middle line:84%
And he said, if I share this
talk, I might be judged.

00:52:35.033 --> 00:52:36.450 align:middle line:84%
If I share this
talk-- and I said,

00:52:36.450 --> 00:52:40.480 align:middle line:84%
yeah, your talk is about
you, but it's not for you.

00:52:40.480 --> 00:52:42.910 align:middle line:84%
It's your story, but
it's a gift to the world.

00:52:42.910 --> 00:52:45.090 align:middle line:84%
And you have to trust
that if you do this

00:52:45.090 --> 00:52:47.530 align:middle line:84%
and you trust this
process and you trust me,

00:52:47.530 --> 00:52:48.790 align:middle line:90%
this is going to be OK.

00:52:48.790 --> 00:52:50.840 align:middle line:84%
This is going to
be more than OK.

00:52:50.840 --> 00:52:53.230 align:middle line:84%
And he shared the day that
he put the barrel of the gun

00:52:53.230 --> 00:52:56.590 align:middle line:84%
into his mouth and had
his finger on the trigger,

00:52:56.590 --> 00:52:59.960 align:middle line:84%
and he was about
to take his life.

00:52:59.960 --> 00:53:03.560 align:middle line:84%
And he remembered that when he
looked or considered suicide

00:53:03.560 --> 00:53:07.220 align:middle line:84%
in the past that three of his
friends came to him and said,

00:53:07.220 --> 00:53:08.915 align:middle line:84%
if you want to kill
yourself, that's OK.

00:53:08.915 --> 00:53:10.410 align:middle line:84%
Well, it's not
OK, but that's OK,

00:53:10.410 --> 00:53:12.550 align:middle line:84%
because we can't prevent
you from doing it.

00:53:12.550 --> 00:53:15.320 align:middle line:84%
But we're going to ask
you to do one thing.

00:53:15.320 --> 00:53:18.480 align:middle line:84%
We're going to ask you to
take a list of our names

00:53:18.480 --> 00:53:20.730 align:middle line:84%
and our numbers, and we're
going to ask you to call us

00:53:20.730 --> 00:53:21.990 align:middle line:90%
to say goodbye before you go.

00:53:21.990 --> 00:53:25.320 align:middle line:90%


00:53:25.320 --> 00:53:27.440 align:middle line:84%
And he said, that
list is the very thing

00:53:27.440 --> 00:53:31.360 align:middle line:84%
that I go to every time I'm
about to commit suicide.

00:53:31.360 --> 00:53:34.950 align:middle line:84%
And he finishes this
extraordinary talk.

00:53:34.950 --> 00:53:36.740 align:middle line:84%
He gets an overwhelming
standing ovation.

00:53:36.740 --> 00:53:38.600 align:middle line:90%
I just-- not this--

00:53:38.600 --> 00:53:39.400 align:middle line:90%
[LIGHT CLAPPING]

00:53:39.400 --> 00:53:40.600 align:middle line:90%
--one person.

00:53:40.600 --> 00:53:42.290 align:middle line:90%
People burst onto their feet.

00:53:42.290 --> 00:53:44.220 align:middle line:84%
They give him a
standing ovation.

00:53:44.220 --> 00:53:46.407 align:middle line:84%
And then I turn it
to the audience.

00:53:46.407 --> 00:53:48.240 align:middle line:84%
And this woman puts her
hand up, and I said,

00:53:48.240 --> 00:53:51.130 align:middle line:84%
would you like-- she says,
why didn't you tell me?

00:53:51.130 --> 00:53:51.930 align:middle line:90%
It's his sister.

00:53:51.930 --> 00:53:54.940 align:middle line:90%


00:53:54.940 --> 00:53:57.740 align:middle line:84%
I said, with respect,
you're making this about you

00:53:57.740 --> 00:53:58.540 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:53:58.540 --> 00:54:02.780 align:middle line:90%


00:54:02.780 --> 00:54:04.962 align:middle line:84%
The next person was
his grandmother.

00:54:04.962 --> 00:54:06.860 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I want
him to know that he

00:54:06.860 --> 00:54:10.150 align:middle line:90%
is loved beyond measure.

